<font color="#FF0000">WINGMAN BY CHOICE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct  4 12:32:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Ed and My Brothers of Choice,<br><br>
I live daily with instruments of war and peace and the science of the stars.  I am privileged.  I have teamed and flown with astronauts and a others, some of which you guys call legends.  Even Spatz would know the name 'Goose&quot; from Top Gun.  Know him (not dead).  Real Guy. Spent a lot of time at &quot;Fighter Town USA&quot; or with one of my old friends who was what the &quot;Flight of the Intruder&quot; depicted.  I was not a Top Gun, but one of the old farts who made their life miserable and honed their capability to survive and improve.  I fold all this around me and fear only when I am too old to not be a part of this.<br><br>
God, I feel privileged to have stood with and for men such as you.  I must confess that I know a great deal about you and have meant it when I say I stand in your shadow.  As Cookie says a True American Hero.  Sorry Spatz needed to know this much.<br><br>
I have improved the warriors capabilities and tactics and am proud I am allowed to continue and participate.  <br><br>
My one real problem when you guys tell your experiences I can't share most of mine.  A part of my world as an aggressor and Strat Recon and other I will not mention.  &quot;Silent Warriors&quot;.  Too bad Doc sees this as cowardice, not security.  We never break the faith.  My four years in Flight Test hold some horrifying experiences (460 sorties), but have nothing to do with the war, but do contribute to who I am.<br><br>
I share this because my brothers of choice must know where I come from and that I am real, not just some Chicken Shit make believe warrior as Doc puts it.<br><br>
Things have been mentioned above as subjects this thread should consider.  Tom, Art, Cook, and Ed have questions unanswered.<br><br>
Ed, Men of honor may fly my wing any time.  I meant it when I said I trust my life with my wing man.  Something we know is not a BS statement.  Many have never been privileged to know men of such honor that you could put your life in their hands without question.  Pity.  Warriors are such men!<br><br>
I to agree that a shot at the &quot;PACK&quot; is a shot me.  A shot at you is a intrusion into my space.  A place I reserve and protect and where you reside.<br>

<p><code>-- triumph7@worldnet.att.net  (SW) </code><p>


